doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199226993.001.0001</li>

<li>Reimer, Marga, 1991, &ldquo;Demonstratives, Demonstrations, and
Demonstrata&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 63(2):
187&ndash;202.</li>

<li>Richard, Mark, 1981, &ldquo;Temporalism and Eternalism&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 39(1): 1&ndash;13.
doi:10.1007/BF00354808</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, &ldquo;What Are Propositions?&rdquo;,
<em>Canadian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 43(5&ndash;6): 702&ndash;719.
doi:10.1080/00455091.2013.870738</li>

<li>Rosen, Gideon, 1997, &ldquo;Who Makes the Rules Around
Here?&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy and Phenomenological Research</em>,
57(1): 163&ndash;171. doi:10.2307/2953786</li>

<li>Rothschild, Daniel, 2007, &ldquo;Presuppositions and
Scope&rdquo;:,<em>Journal of Philosophy</em>, 104(2): 71&ndash;106.
doi:10.5840/jphil2007104233</li>

<li>Rothschild, Daniel and Seth Yalcin, 2016, &ldquo;Three Notions of
Dynamicness in Language&rdquo;, <em>Linguistics and Philosophy</em>,
39(4): 333&ndash;355. doi:10.1007/s10988-016-9188-1</li>

<li>Russell, Bertrand, 1903, <em>The Principles of Mathematics</em>,
Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Salm&oacute;n, Nathan U., 1986, <em>Frege&rsquo;s Puzzle</em>,
Atascadero, CA: Ridgeview Publishing Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1990, &ldquo;A Millian Heir Rejects the
Wages of <em>Sinn</em>&rdquo;, in <em>Propositional Attitudes: The
Role of Content in Logic, Language, and Mind</em>, C. Anthony Anderson
and Joseph Owens (eds.), (CSLI Lecture Notes 20), Stanford, CA: CSLI
Publications.</li>

<li>Searle, John R., 1962, &ldquo;Meaning and Speech Acts&rdquo;,
<em>The Philosophical Review</em>, 71(4): 423&ndash;432.
doi:10.2307/2183455</li>

<li>Schellenberg, Susanna, 2012, &ldquo;Sameness of Fregean
Sense&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 189(1): 163&ndash;175.</li>

<li>Schiffer, Stephen, 1972, <em>Meaning</em>, Oxford: Oxford
University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1987, <em>Remnants of Meaning</em>,
Cambridge, MA: MIT Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;Review: Horwich on
Meaning&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Quarterly</em>, 50(201):
527&ndash;536.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;Two Perspectives on Knowledge
of Language&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Issues</em>, 16: 275&ndash;287.
doi:10.1111/j.1533-6077.2006.00114.x</li>

<li>Schroeder, Mark, 2008, <em>Being For: Evaluating the Semantic
Program of Expressivism</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199534654.001.0001</li>

<li>Sellars, Wilfrid, 1968, <em>Science and Metaphysics: Variations on
Kantian Themes</em>, New York: Humanities Press.</li>

<li>Sider, Theodore, 2011, <em>Writing the Book of the World</em>,
Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199697908.001.0001</li>

<li>Soames, Scott, 1988, &ldquo;Direct Reference, Propositional
Attitudes, and Semantic Content&rdquo;, in <em>Propositions and
Attitudes</em>, Nathan Salm&oacute;n and Scott Soames (eds.), Oxford:
Oxford University Press, 197&ndash;239.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1992, &ldquo;Truth, Meaning, and
Understanding&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 65(1&ndash;2):
17&ndash;35. doi:10.1007/BF00571314</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, &ldquo;Skepticism about Meaning:
Indeterminacy, Normativity, and the Rule-Following Paradox&rdquo;,
<em>Canadian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 27 Supplementary Volume 23:
211&ndash;249. doi:10.1080/00455091.1997.10715967</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, &ldquo;Skepticism About Meaning:
Indeterminacy, Normativity, and the Rule-following Paradox&rdquo;,
<em>Canadian Journal of Philosophy</em> (Supplementary Volume), 23:
211&ndash;249.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, &ldquo;The Modal Argument: Wide Scope
and Rigidified Descriptions&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 32(1):
1&ndash;22. doi:10.1111/0029-4624.00084</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, <em>Beyond Rigidity: The Unfinished
Semantic Agenda of Naming and Necessity</em>, Oxford: Oxford
University Press. doi:10.1093/0195145283.001.0001</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, <em>Philosophy of Language</em>,
Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014. &ldquo;Cognitive Propositions&rdquo;,
in King, Soames, and Speaks 2014: 91&ndash;125.</li>

<li>Sosa, David, 2001, &ldquo;Rigidity in the Scope of Russell&rsquo;s
Theory&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 35(1): 1&ndash;38.
doi:10.1111/0029-4624.00286</li>

<li>Speaks, Jeff, 2014, &ldquo;Propositions Are Properties of
Everything or Nothing&rdquo;, in King, Soames, and Speaks 2014:
71&ndash;90.</li>

<li>Sperber, D. &amp; Wilson, D., 1995, <em>Relevance</em>,
Blackwell.</li>

<li>Stalnaker, Robert C., 1984, <em>Inquiry</em>, Cambridge, MA: MIT
Press.</li>

<li>Stanley, Jason, 2007, <em>Language in Context: Selected
Essays</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Stich, Stephen P. and Ted A. Warfield (eds.), 1994, <em>Mental
Representation: A Reader</em>, Cambridge, MA: Blackwell.</li>

<li>Stojni&#263;, Una, 2019, &ldquo;Content in a Dynamic
Context&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 53(2): 394&ndash;432.
doi:10.1111/nous.12220</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021, <em>Context and Coherence: The Logic
and Grammar of Prominence</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Sullivan, Meghan, 2014, &ldquo;Change We Can Believe In (and
Assert): Change We Can Believe In (and Assert)&rdquo;,
<em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 48(3): 474&ndash;495.
doi:10.1111/j.1468-0068.2012.00874.x</li>

<li>Tarski, Alfred, 1944, &ldquo;The Semantic Conception of Truth: And
the Foundations of Semantics&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy and
Phenomenological Research</em>, 4(3): 341&ndash;376.
doi:10.2307/2102968</li>

<li>Taschek, William W., 1995, &ldquo;Belief, Substitution, and
Logical Structure&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 29(1): 71&ndash;95.
doi:10.2307/2215727</li>

<li>Tillman, Chris &amp; Murray, Adam (eds.) (2022). <em>The Routledge
Handbook of Propositions</em>. Routledge.</li>

<li>Uzquiano, Gabriel, 2015, &ldquo;A Neglected Resolution of
Russell&rsquo;s Paradox of Propositions&rdquo;, <em>Review of Symbolic
Logic</em>, 8(2): 328&ndash;344.</li>

<li>van Inwagen, Peter, 2004, &ldquo;A Theory of Properties&rdquo;, in
<em>Oxford Studies in Metaphysics</em>, volume 1, Dean W Zimmerman
(ed.), Oxford: Clarendon Press, 107&ndash;138.</li>

<li>Weatherson, Brian and Andy Egan, 2011, &ldquo;Introduction:
Epistemic Modals and Epistemic Modality&rdquo;, in Egan and Weatherson
2011: 1&ndash;18. doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199591596.003.0001</li>

<li>Wilson, Deirdre and Dan Sperber, 2012, <em>Meaning and
Relevance</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.
doi:10.1017/CBO9781139028370</li>

<li>Wittgenstein, Ludwig, 1922, <em>Tractatus
Logico-Philosophicus</em>, C. K. Ogden (trans.), London: Routledge
&amp; Kegan Paul; originally published as
&ldquo;Logisch-Philosophische Abhandlung&rdquo;, in <em>Annalen der
Naturphilosophische</em>, XIV (3/4), 1921.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1953, <em>Philosophical
Investigations</em>, G.E.M. Anscombe (trans.), New York:
MacMillan.</li>

<li>Yalcin, Seth, 2007, &ldquo;Epistemic Modals&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>,
116(464): 983&ndash;1026. doi:10.1093/mind/fzm983</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014, &ldquo;Semantics and Metasemantics in
the Context of Generative Grammar&rdquo;, in Burgess and Sherman 2014:
17&ndash;54. doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199669592.003.0002</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2018, &ldquo;Belief as
Question-Sensitive&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy and Phenomenological
Research</em>, 97(1): 23&ndash;47. doi:10.1111/phpr.12330</li>
</ul>
